				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="BattleTech Record Sheets Volume Four: Assault &#039;Mechs" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>From the back of the book:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;100 tons of devastating firepower. Nothing can stand in a BattleMech's way, except another 'Mech! This book compiles for the first time the BattleTech  statistics for the variant Inner Sphere &amp;amp; Clan 'Mech designs. Some are rare, others unique, and each could be that extra surprise you need for victory.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;BattleTech Record Sheets Volume 4: Assault 'Mechs contains assault 'Mech variants from the 2750, 3025, and 3050 eras of BattleMechs. Included are record sheets for over 45 'Mechs, each with full technical statistics. Included are:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;        ANH-1A Annihilator &amp;#10;        IMP-2E Imp &amp;#10;        MAD-4A Marauder II &amp;#10;        SHG-2E Shogun &amp;#10;        THG-11E Thug &amp;#10;        Gladiator A OmniMech &amp;#10;        Masakari C OmniMech&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;User comment:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This record sheet pack is one of four that cover all of the 'Mechs detailed in the BattleTech Technical Readout: 2750, BattleTech Technical Readout: 3025 and BattleTech Technical Readout: 3050. It also includes the current Combat Values for the 'Mechs, as at the time of printing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Although the copyright date states that this publication is copyright 1991, it was actually published in 1990.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
